  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Global Water Initiative (Kenya)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empowering poor rural communities in arid and semi arid zones to reduce their vulnerability to water related shocks and improve their quality of life. Reducing the risk of diseases related to water and environmental hygiene amongst children and mothers in Garissa District.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Target affected populations, assess the state of present water and hygiene facilities, and plan interventions to improve water and hygiene situation, community mobilization, capacity building by training community members in water, sanitation and hygiene practices. The program is now shifting focus to advocate for improved multiple uses of water and for improved watershed governance.</narrative>
  </description>
